'''custom_sea_level''' is a variable of Openttd.cfg file:

Specifies roughly the percentage of the area covered by seas and lakes on a new map, if the [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Quantity sea lakes]] variable has got the value "4" (custom), or, if in the game, in the ''World Generation'' window ''Custom'' is selected at the setting ''Sea level''.

<pre>
[game_creation]
custom_sea_level = 2
</pre>

'''Valid options:''' [ 1 <= n <= 90 ]

'''Default:''' 2


